HEADWORD: Shieldtail
<hw>Shield"tail`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any species of small burrowing snakes of the family
<fam>Uropeltidae</fam>, native of Ceylon and Southern Asia. They have a
small mouth which can not be dilated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shieling</ent>⟦br⟧
